<div class="mt75">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="col-sm-12">
      <div class="col-sm-9">
        <div class="module-detail">
          <h2 class="page-header"> Payroll Management </h2>
          <div class="row mt20 mb80">
            <div class="col-sm-6">
              <a href="javascript:void(0)" data-content="<%= image_path 'modules/payroll/dashboard.png' %>" class="preview-attachment">
                <%= image_tag 'modules/payroll/dashboard.png', class: 'img-responsive' %>
              </a>
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-6">
              All types of salary issue are being merged in payroll module and this management systems has
              lots of standard reports like department wise gross salary, total deduction, net salary, monthly
              employee salary, company wise salary etc. Bonus payments are also automated by Bequent payroll system.
              Other reports like last month salaries, monthly department salary, bonus payment, salary increments.
              So using Bequent web payroll system your payroll process becomes
              very simple & you can import the processed data into your accounting software.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="row mt20 mb80">
            <div class="col-sm-6">
              Salary processing can be done in a few easy steps. You can process full company salary with a button click. Also you can process salary department wise and also employee wise. <br>
              There is a way by which you can able to add multiple category for a employee like Home Allowance, TADA etc. And all of the categories are automatically added or deducted from salary.
              You can modify the automatically calculated data and it will automatically recalculate the net salary.
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-6">
              <a href="javascript:void(0)" data-content="<%= image_path 'modules/payroll/salary_create.png' %>" class="preview-attachment">
                <%= image_tag 'modules/payroll/salary_create.png', class: 'img-responsive' %>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="row mt20 mb80">
            <div class="col-sm-6">
              <a href="javascript:void(0)" data-content="<%= image_path 'modules/payroll/salary_view.png' %>" class="preview-attachment">
                <%= image_tag 'modules/payroll/salary_view.png', class: 'img-responsive' %>
              </a>
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-6">
              You can download your salary payslip if you want. Also it will send a copy of the payslip through email to the employee when you process the salary of that employee.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="row mt20 mb80">
            <div class="col-sm-6">
              Bonus payments are also automated by Bequent payroll system. Just create some category which contains the reason and amount of a bonus payment.
              Then select an employee and create and create a bonus for that employee with a button click.
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-6">
              <a href="javascript:void(0)" data-content="<%= image_path 'modules/payroll/bonus.png' %>" class="preview-attachment">
                <%= image_tag 'modules/payroll/bonus.png', class: 'img-responsive' %>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="row mt20 mb80">
            <div class="col-sm-6">
              <a href="javascript:void(0)" data-content="<%= image_path 'modules/payroll/increment.png' %>" class="preview-attachment">
                <%= image_tag 'modules/payroll/increment.png', class: 'img-responsive' %>
              </a>
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-6">
              You can provide increment from Bequent payroll system without editing the basic salary of an employee.
              That will helps you to find salary increment history of that employee. You need to provide an amount and an effective date,
              our system will automatically add the incremented amount with basic salary on that effective date.
            </div>
          </div>


        </div>
      </div>

      <%= render 'home/feature_modules', modules:@modules %>

    </div>
  </div>


</div>

<script type="text/javascript">
    $(function(){
        $('.preview-attachment').attachmentPreview();
    });
</script>
